branch_understandings.understanding:
The question describes a sequence of events involving "Jerome's" travel to a foreign country.  It details the ages of three "Jerome's" (Jerome, Jerome's brother, and Jerome's cousin) at different times, with the key information being the time it takes for each to travel to the country and the age-related relationship between them.  Specifically, the cousin travels at a rate of 1/4 the speed of Jerome's brother, and the third Jerome travels 10 years slower than the second Jerome.  The question asks for the age-related rate of the third Jerome.

MathML:
```latex
\begin{aligned}
& \text{Jerome's brother travels to a foreign country in 20 years.} \\
& \text{Jerome's cousin travels to a foreign country in 1/4 the time of Jerome's brother.} \\
& \text{Jerome's third travels to a foreign country in 10 years slower than Jerome's second.} \\
& \text{If Jerome's third travels to a foreign country in 60 years, what is the age-related rate of the third?}
\end{aligned}
```
